work approach can inform constructive responses. The book emphasises the need to understand the diverse lives of service users, encouraging readers to share experience and knowledge and to discuss past and present events, to build confidence in tackling injustice at individual and societal levels. As many social workers are becoming disillusioned and dissatisfied with the profession, this book promotes a practice that is rooted in a commitment to positive change and to social justice that will offer a breath of fresh air to students and practitioners alike.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aSocial servicezGreat Britain. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Social Work.2bisacsh1 aWoodward, Rona, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995z9783111196213oZDB-23-BUPP0 cprintz978186134991040uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781447342694?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447342694423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447342694/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-BUPPc1995d2013